This paper discusses security issues in data warehouse environments, which is primarily related to database systems (cs.DB). It also covers various security approaches and their issues, which falls under the category of computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also emphasizes the importance of ensuring the integrity and confidentiality of data, which is a crucial aspect of software engineering (cs.SE). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of machine learning algorithms for detecting anomalies and potential security breaches, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper also touches upon the scalability and performance issues of data warehouse systems, which is related to distributed computing (cs.DC).
